Steps.Message: Update at 20:11 - Our engineers are on their way. At this point we think the issue is a fault on a section of overhead cables that initially interrupted power to 520 properties. However, by rerouting electricity in the area, currently 44 customers are still affected. Using an average timescale, we're estimating power will be on between 22:30 and 23:30 but this may change later. Power back on? To stop receiving texts, just follow this link https://bit.ly/348KOZ3 to unsubscribe.

We became aware of this power cut at 19:57. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way
